<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2016-08-29</DATELINE><TITLE>At the crossroads of autophagy and infection: Noncanonical roles for ATG proteins in viral replication</TITLE><BODY>Autophagy-related (ATG) proteins have increasingly demonstrated functions other than cellular self-eating. In this issue, Mauthe et al. (2016. J. Cell Biol. http://dx.doi.org/10.1083/jcb.201602046) conduct an unbiased RNA interference screen of the ATG proteome to reveal numerous noncanonical roles for ATG proteins during viral infection.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>